Health Minister Zweli Mkhize will on Tuesday visit the Mankweng hospital outside Polokwane where an intern doctor was killed. Xongile Nkhwashu’s remains were found on Sunday night at the doctors’ residence. Mkhize will also convey condolences to the Nkhwashu family at Dzumeri outside Giyani. A suspect known to the deceased has been arrested in connection with the killing. Mkhize says his death is a loss to the health sector. Click below to listen…. <a href="https://iono.fm/e/804216">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>